class="recipe-page--body"><div
class="ad-gpt-main"><div
class="gpt-tag " id="gpt-ad-vertical-top"></div></div><div
class="recipe-page--body-content"><p><span
id="docs-internal-guid-f681a209-3605-789b-fb76-f46643424375" data-redactor-tag="span" data-verified="redactor">For a traditional Blood Mary, you're always going to have Worcestershire, lemon juice, salt, pepper, celery, tomato juice, horseradishprobably tabasco. But if you're feeling adventurous, it's a drink that can benefit from a little experimentation with spice. Things like Sriracha, Chinese mustard, and different types of hot sauce can all create different flavor profiles as well added heat. It all depends on what you prefer really. That said, it's important to start with a classic Bloody Mary and then move on from there. Here's the best recipe to accomplish that. </span></p><p
class="tip">The Classic Bloody Mary</p></div></div><section
class="recipe-container">
<section
class="recipe-info"><div
class="recipe-info-item recipe-info-difficulty">
<span
class="recipe-info-label">Level: </span>
Easy</div>
</section>
<section
class="recipe-content">
<section
class="recipe-ingredients"><h3 class="recipe-section-header">Ingredients</h3><div
class="recipe-ingredients-group-header">The Mix</div><div
class="recipe-ingredients-group"><ul
class="recipe-list recipe-ingredients-list"><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
1/4 c. tomato juice</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
1/4 inch horshradish, chopped</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
1 tsp. Worcestershire</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
3-4 dashes hot sauce (Tabasco, Tapatio, etc.)</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
1/2  lime, fresh squeezed</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
1/2  lemon, fresh squeezed</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
tbsp. vodka</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
dash of black pepper</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
dash of sea salt</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
dash of celery seeds</li></ul></div><div
class="recipe-ingredients-group-header">The Drink</div><div
class="recipe-ingredients-group"><ul
class="recipe-list recipe-ingredients-list"><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
2 oz. vodka</li><li
class="recipe-ingredients-item" itemprop="ingredients">
6-8 oz. Bloody Mary mix</li></ul></div>
</section>
<section
class="recipe-directions"><h3 class="recipe-section-header">Directions</h3><ol
class="recipe-list recipe-directions-list" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><li
class="recipe-directions-item">Blend horseradish, Worcestershire, celery seeds, and tomato juice until smooth.</li><li
class="recipe-directions-item">Add lemon, lime, hot sauce, salt, and pepper.</li><li
class="recipe-directions-item">Adjust the mix to taste depending on how spicy, salty, or citrusy you like it.</li><li
class="recipe-directions-item">Add a tablespoon of vodka to stabilize the mix and keep the juices fresh.</li><li
class="recipe-directions-item">Combine 6-8 ounces of the mix with 2 ounces of vodka into a glass. Pour back and forth into another glass with ice 3 or 4 times to mix.</li><li
class="recipe-directions-item">Garnish with a celery stalk and a lime, or whatever else you feel like adding. Sky's the limit.</li></ol>
</section>
<section
class="recipe-extra-content"><blockquote><p><strong>Garnish Suggestions: </strong>Lemon wedge, pepperoncini, cherry peppers with feta, shrimp cocktail, pickled green beans, garlic dill pickle spears, and of course, the classic celery stalk.</p></blockquote></section>
</section>
